```python
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
df_event = pd.DataFrame({
    "user_id": ["U1","U1","U1","U2","U2","U3","U3","U4","U4"],
    "event": ["signup","view","purchase",
              "signup","view",
              "signup","purchase",
              "signup","view"],
    "day": [1,2,5, 1,3, 2,4, 1,6]
})

df_channel = pd.DataFrame({
    "user_id": ["U1","U2","U3","U4"],
    "channel": ["AD","AD","ORG","ORG"]
})
display(df_event, df_channel)
```

# ÌíÄÏù¥

```python
df_event["is_signup"] = df_event["event"].eq("signup")
df_event["is_purchase"] = df_event["event"].eq("purchase")
signup_day = (
    df_event[df_event["is_signup"]]
    .groupby("user_id", as_index=False)["day"]
    .min()
    .rename(columns={"day": "signup_day"})
)
purchase_day = (
    df_event[df_event["is_purchase"]]
    .groupby("user_id", as_index=False)["day"]
    .min()
    .rename(columns={"day": "purchase_day"})
)
user_feat = signup_day.merge(purchase_day, how="left", on="user_id")
user_feat['lag_days']=np.where(user_feat['purchase_day'].notna(), user_feat['purchase_day']-user_feat['signup_day'], np.nan)
display(user_feat)
user_feat['is_converted'] = user_feat['purchase_day'].notna()
user_feat = user_feat.merge(df_channel, on="user_id", how="left")
converted = user_feat[user_feat["is_converted"]]
display(user_feat, converted)
# df_merged = user_feat.merge(df_channel, how='left', on='user_id')
# display(df_merged)
channel_feat = user_feat.groupby('channel').agg(
    users = ('user_id', 'count'),
    converted_users = ('is_converted', 'sum'),
    avg_lag = ('lag_days', 'mean'),
).reset_index()
channel_feat['conversion_rate']=channel_feat['converted_users']/channel_feat['users']
channel_feat = channel_feat.sort_values(by='conversion_rate', ascending=False)
display(channel_feat)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
fig1, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(7,4))
ax1.bar(channel_feat['channel'], channel_feat['conversion_rate'])
ax1.axhline(0.5, color='gray', linestyle='--')
ax1.grid(False)
ax1.set_title("Conversion Rate by Channel")
fig2, ax2 = plt.subplots(figsize=(7,4))
data = [
    converted[converted["channel"]=="AD"]["lag_days"],
    converted[converted["channel"]=="ORG"]["lag_days"]
]
ax2.boxplot(data)
ax2.set_xticks([1,2])
ax2.set_xticklabels(["AD","ORG"])

ax2.set_title("Purchase Lag Distribution by Channel")
ax2.set_xlabel("channel")
ax2.set_ylabel("lag_days")
ax2.grid(False)

plt.show()
